      "date": "2012-12-02 22:06:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nFirst, thanknuou dor including the commit hashes of the patvhes from master. This makes it easier to track the original patch. \n\nThere are a few style issues that I would have asked you to fix if this patch was landing on master, but since it is a backport of an existing patch I don't see much value in changing them only for the b2_1 landing.  I only mention them here so you know for future patches:\n\n- console messages (CERROR, CWARN) should be of the form:\n\n        CERROR(\"%s: message goes here: rc = %d\\n\",\n               device_name, rc);\n\nFor messages in llite the device_name should be th fsname. \n\n- no need for linefeed escape '\\' after \"||\" or \"&&\" or \"|\" at the end of test_24b",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
